# ReactJS E-Commerce Application Deployment using Docker, Jenkins and AWS

## Project Overview

This project demonstrates the deployment of a ReactJS E-Commerce application using Docker, Docker Compose, Jenkins CI/CD, GitHub, Docker Hub, AWS EC2, and Prometheus-Grafana Monitoring.

The objective is to automate the build, deployment, and monitoring of the application using DevOps tools and best practices.

---

## Technologies Used

- ReactJS
- Docker
- Docker Compose
- Bash Scripting
- Git & GitHub
- Docker Hub
- Jenkins
- AWS EC2
- Prometheus
- Node Exporter
- Grafana

---

## Project Workflow

1. Clone the ReactJS application from GitHub.
2. Build the application.
3. Dockerize the application using Dockerfile.
4. Create a Docker Compose configuration.
5. Automate Docker build using build.sh.
6. Automate deployment using deploy.sh.
7. Push source code to GitHub Dev branch.
8. Configure Jenkins for Continuous Integration and Continuous Deployment.
9. Push Docker images to Docker Hub.
10. Deploy the application on AWS EC2.
11. Monitor the server and application using Prometheus and Grafana.

---

