---

## Docker

### Build Docker Image

```bash
docker build -t devops-build:v1 .
```

### Run Docker Container

```bash
docker run -d -p 80:80 devops-build:v1
```

### Docker Compose

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

---

## Bash Scripts

### Build Script

```bash
chmod +x build.sh
./build.sh
```

### Deploy Script

```bash
chmod +x deploy.sh
./deploy.sh
```

---

## Git Commands

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Initial Commit"
git push -u origin dev
```

---

## Docker Hub

### Development Repository

```
jude795/dev
```

### Production Repository

```
jude795/prod
```

Development images are pushed to the **dev** repository, while production images are pushed to the **prod** repository after merging the Dev branch into the Master branch.

---

## Jenkins Pipeline

The Jenkins pipeline performs the following tasks automatically:

- Pull latest source code from GitHub
- Build Docker Image
- Push Docker Image to Docker Hub
- Deploy Docker Container
- Trigger builds automatically using GitHub Webhooks

---

## AWS Deployment

The application is deployed on an AWS EC2 t2.micro instance.

Configured Security Group Ports:

| Port | Purpose |
|------|---------|
|22|SSH (My IP)|
|80|HTTP|
|8080|Jenkins|
|9090|Prometheus|
|9100|Node Exporter|

---

## Monitoring

Monitoring is implemented using:

- Prometheus
- Node Exporter
- Grafana

The monitoring dashboard continuously tracks system performance and application health.

---

## Application Access

Application

```
http://<EC2-PUBLIC-IP>
```

Jenkins

```
http://<EC2-PUBLIC-IP>:8080
```

Prometheus

```
http://<EC2-PUBLIC-IP>:9090
```

Node Exporter

```
http://<EC2-PUBLIC-IP>:9100
```

Grafana

```
http://<EC2-PUBLIC-IP>:3000
```

